details.description:
The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Dodgers pays tribute to the city of Los Angeles and its storied sports culture, blending Kobe Bryant’s legendary basketball legacy with the iconic colors of the Dodgers. This sleek sneaker features a game royal snakeskin-textured upper, accented with white midsoles and red jersey-style number 8 detailing on the lateral ankle. The baseball-inspired stitching on the tongue ties the theme together, making this pair a standout tribute to both Kobe and LA’s baseball dynasty.

Designed for performance and style, the Kobe 6 Protro Dodgers retains the responsive Zoom Air cushioning and lightweight build that made the original a go-to on the court. Whether you’re playing ball or rocking them casually, the combination of storytelling and signature Protro upgrades ensures a perfect balance of comfort and durability. The shoe’s sleek silhouette and city-inspired details make it a must-have for both Lakers and Dodgers fans alike.

Released on May 30, 2025, for a retail price of $190, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Dodgers celebrates the deep connection between Kobe Bryant and Los Angeles sports culture. With its nods to baseball and basketball history, this release is a true collector’s item.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Sail All-Star brings a fresh twist to an iconic silhouette. This edition stands out with its sail-dominated upper, offset by a striking black Swoosh and subtle platinum violet accents. Unlike previous versions of the Kobe 6, this release introduces a bold new starry pattern on the upper, replacing the signature snakeskin texture on the medial sides of the upper. This design choice not only elevates the shoe’s visual appeal but also nods to Kobe Bryant’s star power and celebrates the 2025 NBA all star weekend, making it a must-have for collectors and hoopers alike.

Further refining its look, the sneaker features light bone tones across the midsole and heel, creating a balanced contrast with the white outsole. The platinum violet lining adds a unique pop of color without overpowering the shoe’s clean aesthetic. Performance-wise, the Kobe 6 Protro maintains its low-cut profile and responsive cushioning, ensuring optimal comfort on and off the court. Whether styled casually or laced up for a game, this pair seamlessly merges function with fashion.

Released on February 13, 2025, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Sail All-Star hit shelves at a retail price of $190, quickly becoming a sought-after addition to the Kobe lineup. Its refined blend of sail, black, light bone, white, and platinum violet gives it a timeless appeal, while the innovative design elements make it a standout among past iterations.

Step into the future while honoring a legend with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch. This long-awaited sneaker, flips the script on the iconic Grinch colorway. Boasting a Bright Crimson upper that mirrors the intensity of Kobe's game, this shoe is a standout piece in any collection. The snakeskin-textured upper, a nod to the Black Mamba himself, is complemented by black Swooshes and electrifying Electric Green accents.

The Reverse Grinch doesn't just turn heads with its colorway; it pays homage to Kobe Bryant's enduring legacy. Electric Green laces and Kobe branding on the tongues and heels add to its unique charm. The midsole and heel counter, wrapped in Bright Crimson, maintain the shoe’s bold and cohesive look, ensuring it stands out on the court and in the streets.

Set to release on December 16, 2023, for $190, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch is more than a sneaker—it's a tribute to a basketball icon. With its vivid colors and sleek design, it's a must-have for sneakerheads and basketball fans alike.

The Nike Kobe 6 Sail All-Star (GS) updates the Kobe 6 in a neutral colorway of Sail, Light Bone, and white with contrasting accents in black and soft Platinum Violet.

Instead of the original textile pattern, the Sail All-Star (GS) Nike Kobe 6 covers the upper in a raised star pattern, adding dimension to the shoe. The upper‚Äôs predominant Sail hue draws inspiration from a snake shedding its skin and revealing something new. Additional hits of Sail can be found on the midsole and tongue, while Light Bone adds a complementary creamy tone to the heel and grippy outsole. The signature Swoosh logo checks across the side panel in black, while Kobe‚Äôs signature sheath logo decorates the tongue‚Äî also in black.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the subtle contrast provided by Platinum Violet on the lining. It almost blends into the Sail upper but catches the eye upon close inspection. The grade school-sized Nike Kobe 6 Sail All-Star (GS) was released on February 13, 2025, and sold for $125.

Nike opened a new chapter at the end of 2020 and refreshed the Kobe 6 design with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch. The Kobe 6 Grinch originally debuted in 2010 when Kobe Bryant’s Los Angeles Lakers faced LeBron James’ Miami Heat in a legendary match up on Christmas Day. This is the first Kobe 6 to receive the Kobe Protro treatment, a design process that takes classic Kobe designs and updates them with modern tech for improved performance.

At a first glance, the Nike Kobe 6 Grinch looks identically like the OG pair from 2010: it features a Green Apple and Volt textured, snake-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba moniker. A black Swoosh, red Kobe branding on the tongue, and green translucent outsole accentuate the shoe’s reptile theme. But, because this is a Protro, there are some differences. The updated Kobe 6 Grinch arrives with a more responsive Zoom Air cushioning system and scaled-down traction for an improved court feel. The silhouette shape is even altered to provide a lower, sleeker fit.

The Nike Kobe 6 Grinch released in December of 2020 and retailed for $180.

name: Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch

details.description:
The Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch dresses the Vapor Edge Kobe 6 in a vibrant green colorway inspired by Dr. Seuss’s beloved Christmas character.

The Grinch Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE reimagines Kobe Bryant’s recognizable basketball shoe for the football field. For instance, it boasts sturdy studs placed across the outsole plate in a wide pattern. However, what makes this sneaker stand out is its Grinch-inspired colors, including Green Apple and Volt. The upper features a layer of durable TPU and snake-skin patterns in Green Apple. Adding contrast, black Swoosh logos reach across the side panels, while Bryant’s signature sheathed sword logo in Bright Crimson decorates the tongue. Other Bright Crimson details can be found on Bryant’s signature and details across the outsole.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the shoe’s form-fitting design supported by Vaper Edge technology underfoot. The Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch was released on November 22, 2024, and sold for $230.

Introducing the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo 2024, a sleek rendition of the classic Kobe 6, set to captivate with its unique camouflage pattern inspired by Kobe Bryant's early years in Italy. The colorway, a sophisticated blend of black, crimson bog, and khaki, is a stylish nod to Kobe's formative experiences and his enduring legacy. Tailored for those who admire the subtleties of design and the stories behind them, this sneaker combines the essence of Kobe's history with cutting-edge footwear technology.

The Kobe 6 Protro isn't just about its standout Italian Camo aesthetic; it's a powerhouse of sneaker tech. The shoe is engineered with advanced performance features like Zoom Air cushioning for responsive comfort, a Cushlon midsole for lightweight support, and a durable outsole that pays homage to Kobe's multidirectional playing style. The sneaker's unique texture mimics a snake's skin, reflecting Kobe's "Black Mamba" persona, while the innovative tech ensures these shoes stand up to the demands of both performance and everyday wear.

On April 13, 2024, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo dropped at a retail price of $190. This release offers a piece of basketball royalty's origin story, wrapped in modern performance and timeless design. Embrace the spirit of Kobe's legacy and add a touch of Italian finesse to your sneaker collection with this 2024 re-release. It's a sneaker that celebrates history, innovation, and the endless pursuit of greatness, perfect for those who walk the path less traveled.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 pays tribute to the late Gigi Bryant and the Mamba & Mambacita Sports Foundation.

The Nike Kobe 6 debuted in 2011 and was the sixth signature sneaker between Nike and the late Laker legend, Kobe Bryant. In 2018, Nike would retro some of Kobe’s older and most memorable sneakers under their Protro program as a means to better equip each pair for the demands and needs of current athletes.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 features a black snakeskin-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba on-court moniker. From there, Gigi’s AAU basketball jersey number, 2, is stamped on both lateral sides of the ankle. The Mamba & Mambacita Sports Foundation crest is printed on the heel of each shoe followed by both Kobe and Gigi’s names underneath. Lastly, a neoprene and mesh tongue and signature Zoom midsole provide comfort and stability on and off the court.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 released on May 1st, 2022.
DISCLAIMER: All Grade School Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch's will come in the standard Nike orange box.

name: Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch Mismatch

details.description: The Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch Mismatch is a striking tribute to the legendary Kobe Bryant, combining his iconic basketball sneaker design with cutting-edge football cleat technology. This unique footwear features a vibrant green colorway reminiscent of the beloved 'Grinch' edition, but with a twist - the left and right shoes sport slightly different color schemes, creating an eye-catching mismatch effect. The upper is crafted with lightweight, breathable materials to ensure optimal performance on the field, while the Vapor Edge sole provides superior traction and agility for quick cuts and explosive movements. Designed for the gridiron, these cleats incorporate elements from Kobe's signature basketball shoe, seamlessly blending style with functionality. The Green Apple, Black, Volt, and Bright Crimson color combination not only pays homage to the original Kobe 6 'Grinch' but also adds a fresh, modern touch to football footwear. With a retail price of $230 and a release date set for December 23, 2024, these cleats are poised to become a must-have for both Kobe fans and football players alike. Our team thinks this product is great for athletes looking to stand out on the field while honoring the legacy of one of basketball's greatest players.

name: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Challenge Red All-Star (2021)

details.description:
Nike brought back an NBA All-Star classic with the re-release of the Nike Kobe 6 All-Star. The Kobe 6 All-Star originally debuted in the 2011 All-Star Game, where Kobe Bryant took home his fourth All-Star MVP. In the game, Kobe dropped 37 points, grabbed 14 rebounds, and notched a win for the West in a close match-up against LeBron and the East.

Like most Kobe Protros, the Kobe 6 Protro All-Star is constructed differently than the 2011 model. Its design is lower, sleeker, and features updated technology for improved on-court performance. A flexible Air Zoom Turbo unit in the midsole and an outsole with scaled-down traction enhance responsiveness and court grip. The upper is composed of a red and black snakeskin-textured material, nodding to Kobe’s Black Mamba moniker. A black heel cap donning Kobe’s signature wraps up the design.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro All-Star released in March of 2021 and retailed for $180.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024) (GS) represents an installment of the continued Nike Kobe line that honors the legacy of NBA star Kobe Bryant. This colorway pays homage to his time spent in Italy, where his father played pro basketball. This sneaker is sized for grade-school-aged kids.

The big kids’ Italian Camo colorway of the Kobe 6 Protro 2024 features a synthetic upper with a faux reptile texture. The camo pattern takes inspiration from the Italian military uniform. Black laces close over a black tongue to ensure a snug closure. An olive green TPU heel counter completes the look of this upper. The Protro midsole in black rests atop a rubber outsole in olive green and black.

What we enjoy most about this sneaker are the hits of crimson that add pops of contrast throughout the sneaker. Bright red Kobe logos hit the tongue tag and outsole, while the tongue lining and side panel Nike swoosh are also bright red. The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024) (GS) was released on April 13, 2024, for $120 retail.

name: Nike Kobe 6 Black Mamba Collection Fade to Black

details.description:
The Nike Kobe 6 Grinch (2010) is a limited-edition sneaker that was inspired by the Dr. Seuss character, the Grinch. It comes in a Lime Green accent with Varsity Red and black accents.

The Kobe 6 Grinch (2010) features Flywire technology and Lime Green round laces. The midsole is made using Lunarlon foam technology, while the outsole has a rubber construction with a herringbone pattern. The insole is designed with a molded sock liner that includes perforations and the forefoot incorporates Nike's Zoom Air cushioning technology. The Mamba logo features on the tongue and a Kobe signature is seen on the heel.

We believe that one of the noteworthy features of the Nike Kobe 6 Grinch (2010) is its textured upper, which includes a scale-like pattern that represents Mamba skin and is a nod to Bryant's nickname, the Black Mamba. The shoe was released on December 25th, 2010, at a retail price of $130.
